main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted by personnel in Los Alamos, New Mexico on 23 November 1954.
interesting points: The object was silver in color and emitted no sound,The sighting lasted for 10 minutes,Two F-84 jets were diverted to investigate but found no results,The object was speculated to be a civilian transport due to a temperature inversion effect,Insufficient data was found for conclusive evaluation.
witness description: personnel observing from the control tower
